  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-05-03 00:48 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] HL telemetry now exposes execution_mode directly\n\n**Task:** Add a first-class HL execution mode to live telemetry so dashboard/monitoring can distinguish funded monitor mode from fully tradeable mode without inferring from multiple fields.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P3**.\n- Prior HL telemetry exposed the raw ingredients: `wallet_blocked=false`, `order_notional_blocked=true`, `planned_order_notional=11.217492`, `min_order_notional_usd=20.0`.\n- But `status` was still generically `live`, which could be misread as live-tradeable.\n- I patched `/home/ubuntu/clawd/hyperliquid-trader/hl_live_trader.py` so `write_live_state()` now computes execution modes:\n  - `wallet_blocked` when balance is below `$10`\n  - `notional_blocked` when wallet is funded but planned order notional is below `$20`\n  - `live_tradeable` when both gates pass\n- The payload now includes a dedicated `execution_mode` field and sets default `status` to the same mode.\n- Validation passed:\n  - `python3 -m py_compile /home/ubuntu/clawd/hyperliquid-trader/hl_live_trader.py` \u2705\n  - direct write test produced `execution_mode=notional_blocked` \u2705\n  - restarted only `hl-bot` \u2705\n  - post-restart live state shows `status=notional_blocked`, `execution_mode=notional_blocked`, balance `37.391639`, planned order notional `11.217492`, min order notional `20.0`, `wallet_blocked=false`, positions `0`, signals `0` \u2705\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p3-hl-execution-mode-telemetry-2026-05-03-0048.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** This removes ambiguity: HL is healthy and funded, but not fully tradeable under current risk settings. Dashboard consumers can now read one field (`execution_mode`) instead of reconstructing intent from balance and notional gates.\n\n**Decision:** Keep HL running. Mark current HL execution mode as **notional_blocked**. Do not raise risk to force trades. Use `execution_mode` as canonical dashboard/monitoring state going forward.\n\n**Next:** Update any dashboard reader that still treats `status=live` as the only healthy/tradeable indicator. If the dashboard already displays raw HL balance only, add/consume `execution_mode` so notional-blocked is visible.\n\n## 2026-05-03 00:44 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] Post-midnight shadow tape says V5a still matters\n\n**Task:** Continue P2 reject-reason shadow tracking after midnight while waiting for the first settled PM outcome rows with alpha-context tags.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P2**.\n- Realized outcomes still have **0 alpha-tagged rows** out of **201** total; no new settled PM trades since instrumentation.\n- Current alpha context remains cautionary despite low PM risk: classifier **mixed_transition**, PM risk **low**, fast regime **RANGE**, breakout risk **expanding**, sentiment regime **sentiment_impulse_up**, transi",
